137
00:15:12,696 --> 00:15:14,687
No. Frederick.

138
00:15:14,776 --> 00:15:17,848
Well, why isn't it Frodorick Fronkonsteen?

139
00:15:17,936 --> 00:15:20,450
It isn't. It's Frederick Fronkonsteen.

140
00:15:20,536 --> 00:15:22,731
I see.

141
00:15:22,816 --> 00:15:26,206
- You must be Igor.
- No. It's pronounced I-gor.

142
00:15:27,616 --> 00:15:31,655
- But they told me it was Igor.
- Well, they were wrong then, weren't they?

143
00:15:32,616 --> 00:15:35,050
You were sent by Herr Falkstein, weren't you?

144
00:15:35,136 --> 00:15:38,970
Yes. My grandfather
used to work for your grandfather.

145
00:15:41,776 --> 00:15:44,734
- How nice.
- Of course, the rates have gone up.

146
00:15:44,816 --> 00:15:48,411
Of course. I'm sure we'll get along splendidly.

147
00:15:49,856 --> 00:15:52,416
Sorry. I...

148
00:15:53,136 --> 00:15:57,175
You know, I don't mean to embarrass you,
but I'm a rather brilliant surgeon.

149
00:15:57,256 --> 00:15:59,690
Perhaps I could help you with that hump.

150
00:15:59,776 --> 00:16:01,767
What hump?

151
00:16:06,176 --> 00:16:08,053
Let's go.

152
00:16:08,136 --> 00:16:11,208
Allow me, master.

153
00:16:11,296 --> 00:16:13,287
Thanks very much.

154
00:16:16,936 --> 00:16:19,370
Walk this way.

155
00:16:21,096 --> 00:16:23,087
This way.

