- Where is my grandfather's private library?
- I don't know what you mean, sir.

200
00:21:10,016 --> 00:21:14,009
Well, these books are very general.
Any doctor might have them in his study.

201
00:21:14,096 --> 00:21:18,089
This is the only library I know of,
Dr Frankenstone.

202
00:21:18,936 --> 00:21:21,291
- Fronkonsteen.
- Fronkonsteen.

203
00:21:22,016 --> 00:21:24,405
Well, we'll see.

204
00:21:25,256 --> 00:21:27,247
Good night.

205
00:21:29,456 --> 00:21:32,812
Would the doctor care for
a brandy before retiring?

206
00:21:33,736 --> 00:21:36,330
No. Thank you.

207
00:21:38,376 --> 00:21:40,367
Some warm milk...

208
00:21:41,336 --> 00:21:43,133
..perhaps?

209
00:21:43,936 --> 00:21:46,609
No, thank you very much.

210
00:21:46,696 --> 00:21:48,732
No, thanks.

211
00:21:48,816 --> 00:21:50,807
Ovaltine?

212
00:21:54,976 --> 00:21:56,728
Nothing.

213
00:21:56,816 --> 00:21:58,568
Thank you.

214
00:21:58,656 --> 00:22:00,965
