ofthe bookcase.

256
00:25:28,816 --> 00:25:31,330
Is that perfectly clear?

257
00:25:32,496 --> 00:25:34,487
I think so.

258
00:25:42,656 --> 00:25:44,647
Good girl.

259
00:25:45,696 --> 00:25:48,654
Put the candle back.

260
00:25:55,736 --> 00:25:58,170
Oh, look, Doctor. A passageway.

261
00:25:58,256 --> 00:26:01,214
Whatever that music is,
it's coming from down there.

262
00:26:01,296 --> 00:26:04,811
- I'd better take a look.
- Oh, let me come with you, Doctor, please.

263
00:26:04,896 --> 00:26:06,887
I don't wanna stay up here alone.

264
00:26:06,976 --> 00:26:09,888
All right, then.
Close your robe and follow me.

265
00:26:09,976 --> 00:26:11,967
Oh, Doctor. The candle...

266
00:26:12,736 --> 00:26:15,330
Good thinking. Let's try this one.

267
00:26:16,536 --> 00:26:18,527
Stand back!

268
00:26:50,456 --> 00:26:52,845
Don't be frightened, dear. Just a rat.

269
00:26:53,576 --> 00:26:55,931
A filthy, slimy rat.

270
00:27:30,456 --> 00:27:32,447
Good Lord!

271
00:27:51,176 --> 00:27:52,814
I-l-l-l-l-l

272
00:27:52,896 --> 00:27:55,205
Ain't got nobody

273
00:27:55,296 --> 00:27:58,606
And nobody cares for me

274
00:27:59,976 --> 00:28:01,455
- I-gor.
- Frodorick.

275
00:28:01,536 --> 00:28:03,527
How did you get here?

276
00:28:05,056 --> 00:28:08,890
Through the dumbwaiter. I heard
strange music from the upstairs kitchen

277
00:28:08,976 --> 00:28:11,206
and I just followed it down.

278
00:28:11,296 --> 00:28:14,254
Call it... a hunch.

279
00:28:14,776 --> 00:28:18,735
- There must have been someone else here.
- It would seem that way.

280
00:28:18,816 --> 00:28:21,569
And there's the only other door.

281
00:28:21,656 --> 00:28:23,647
Wait, master.

282
00:28:23,736 --> 00:28:25,727
It might be dangerous.

283
00:28:26,536 --> 00:28:28,527
You go first.

284
00:28:39,416 --> 00:28:41,805
Aren't there any lights in this place?

285
00:28:42,816 --> 00:28:47,287
Two nasty-looking switches over here,
but I'm not going to be the first.

286
00:28:52,216 --> 00:28:54,207
Damn your eyes.

287
00:28:54,296 --> 00:28:56,287
Too late.

288
00:29:08,576 --> 00:29:11,568
So this is where it all happened.

289
00:29:22,216 --> 00:29:26,846
Just think. A deadbrain
ready to live again in a newbody.

290
00:29:27,416 --> 00:29:30,294
Look. No blood, no decomposition.

291
00:29:30,376 --> 00:29:32,367
Justa fewsutures.

292
00:29:32,456 --> 00:29:35,050
- Throw the main switch.
- Yes, master.

293
00:29:41,576 --> 00:29:43,851
What a filthy mess.

294
00:29:43,936 --> 00:29:47,611
I dunno. A little paint, a few flowers,
couple ofthrow pillows...

295
00:29:51,496 --> 00:29:56,047
Well, it seems as if our mysterious violinist
has disa...p...

296
00:29:56,136 --> 00:29:58,809
- Disa... what?
- ..peared.

297
00:29:58,896 --> 00:30:02,491
There is a light
coming from behind that door.

298
00:30:04,776 --> 00:30:06,767
Follow me.

299
00:30:33,416 --> 00:30:35,407
Doctor, look!

300
00:30:37,176 --> 00:30:40,691
Well... This explains the music.

301
00:30:42,176 --> 00:30:44,087
It's still warm.

302
00:30:44,176 --> 00:30:46,087
But who was playing it?

303
00:30:46,176 --> 00:30:47,689
I don't know.

304
00:30:47,776 --> 00:30:51,451
But whoever it was just barely finished
putting out his cigar.

305
00:30:51,536 --> 00:30:54,096
Such strange goings-on.

306
00:30:56,456 --> 00:30:58,447
What is this place?

307
00:30:58,536 --> 00:31:00,925
Music room?

308
00:31:01,016 --> 00:31:03,928
But there's nothing here
but books and papers.

309
00:31:04,416 --> 00:31:06,407
Books and papers?

310
00:31:07,216 --> 00:31:08,615
It is!

311
00:31:08,696 --> 00:31:11,972
This is my grandfather's private library.
I feel it.

312
00:31:13,336 --> 00:31:15,327
Look! Look at this.

313
00:31:29,136 --> 00:31:33,971
"..until, from the midst ofthis
darkness, a sudden light broke in upon me."

314
00:31:34,936 --> 00:31:39,214
"A light so brilliant and wondrous,
and yet so simple."

315
00:31:40,296 --> 00:31:42,730
"Change the poles from plus to minus

316
00:31:43,736 --> 00:31:46,569
and from minus to plus."

317
00:31:50,136 --> 00:31:54,254
"I alone succeeded in discovering
the secret of bestowing life."

318
00:31:54,896 --> 00:31:56,727
"Nay, even more..."

319
00:31:56,816 --> 00:32:01,890
"I myself became capable
of bestowing animation

320
00:32:02,696 --> 00:32:05,005
upon lifeless matter."

321
00:32:11,896 --> 00:32:15,013
It could work.

322
00:32:31,976 --> 00:32:34,490
- Kipper?
- Thank you, Doctor.

323
00:32:39,896 --> 00:32:43,093
"As the minuteness ofthe parts
formed a hindrance to my speed,

324
00:32:43,176 --> 00:32:48,614
I resolved therefore
to make the creature of a gigantic stature."

325
00:32:51,136 --> 00:32:52,808
Of course.

326
00:32:52,896 --> 00:32:54,966
That would simplify everything.

327
00:32:55,056 --> 00:32:56,614
In other words,

328
00:32:56,696 --> 00:33:01,372
his veins, his feet, his hands, his organs
would all have to be increased in size.

329
00:33:01,456 --> 00:33:03,367
Exactly.

330
00:33:04,176 --> 00:33:06,815
He would have an enormous Schwanzstuck.

331
00:33:12,536 --> 00:33:14,686
That goes without saying.

332
00:33:14,776 --> 00:33:16,175
Woof.

333
00:33:17,136 --> 00:33:19,570
He's gonna be very popular.

334
00:33:20,376 --> 00:33:25,655
So then. What we're aiming for is a being
approximately seven feet in height,

335
00:33:25,736 --> 00:33:30,526
with all features either congenitally
or artificially proportionate in size.

336
00:33:30,616 --> 00:33:32,413
Something like...

337
00:33:32,856 --> 00:33:34,892
..this?

338
00:33:38,936 --> 00:33:40,688
Hello...

339
00:33:40,776 --> 00:33:42,767
You've caught something there.

340
00:33:42,856 --> 00:33:46,326
Crude, yes, primitive, yes,
perhaps even grotesque,

341
00:33:46,416 --> 00:33:49,089
yet something inexplicable tells me

342
00:33:49,896 --> 00:33:54,048
that this might be our man.

343
00:34:09,496 --> 00:34:11,487
All right, all right.

344
00:34:11,576 --> 00:34:14,010
That's good enough for the likes of 'im.

345
00:34:30,336 --> 00:34:32,327
Get down, you fool.

346
00:34:40,376 --> 00:34:42,367
Now.

347
00:35:10,176 --> 00:35:12,167
What a filthyjob.

348
00:35:12,616 --> 00:35:14,846
- Could be worse.
- How?

349
00:35:14,936 --> 00:35:16,927
Could be raining.

350
00:36:02,176 --> 00:36:04,371
Quick.

351
00:36:08,536 --> 00:36:10,413
Need a hand?

352
00:36:10,496 --> 00:36:13,966
No, thanks. I have one.
Thanks very much all the same.

353
00:36:14,056 --> 00:36:15,694
Just a moment, sir.

354
00:36:15,776 --> 00:36:19,485
I know everyone around here,
but I've never seen your face before.

355
00:36:19,576 --> 00:36:21,567
Can you account for yourself?

356
00:36:21,656 --> 00:36:25,649
Yes. I am Dr Frederick Fronkonsteen,
newly arrived from America.

357
00:36:25,736 --> 00:36:28,330
Oh, yes, sir. I was told you were here.

358
00:36:28,416 --> 00:36:31,567
Well, I'm Constable Henry, sir.
Pleased to meet you.

359
00:36:33,216 --> 00:36:35,525
How very nice to meet you, Constable.

360
00:36:35,616 --> 00:36:38,528
Why, you're chilled to the bone, sir.

361
00:36:38,616 --> 00:36:41,528
A nice, warm fire would be the thing for you.

362
00:36:41,616 --> 00:36:44,892
A little nip from the old bottle
wouldn't be too bad either, sir.

363
00:36:44,976 --> 00:36:47,171
That's the ticket, yes.

364
00:36:47,256 --> 00:36:50,692
Well, ifyou have everything in hand, sir,
I'll say good night.

365
00:36:50,776 --> 00:36:52,767
Thank you very much, Constable.

366
00:36:52,856 --> 00:36:55,768
At your service, sir, always.

367
00:36:57,576 --> 00:37:00,249
- Good night, Constable.
- Good night, sir.

368
00:37:16,936 --> 00:37:19,689
Oh, what an awesome sight.

369
00:37:21,016 --> 00:37:24,611
What a profound and reverend night is this.

370
00:37:25,856 --> 00:37:28,131
With such a specimen for a body,

371
00:37:28,696 --> 00:37:32,894
all we need now is
an equally magnificent brain.

372
00:37:34,816 --> 00:37:37,649
- You know what to do?
- I have a pretty good idea.

373
00:37:37,736 --> 00:37:39,727
Good man.

374
00:37:40,376 --> 00:37:43,607
Didn't you... Didn't you use to have that
on the other side?

375
00:37:43,696 --> 00:37:45,687
- What?
- Your...

376
00:37:46,576 --> 00:37:48,567
Never mind.

377
00:37:52,096 --> 00:37:55,611
- Do you have that name I gave you?
- I have it written down.

378
00:37:56,736 --> 00:38:00,934
- H Delbruck.
- Hans Delbruck.

379
00:39:49,016 --> 00:39:52,645
- He is hideous.
- He's beautiful.

380
00:39:53,736 --> 00:39:57,092
And he is mine.

381
00:40:04,736 --> 00:40:07,489
Hurry now.
We're fighting time and the elements.

382
00:40:07,576 --> 00:40:11,489
- Are you ready?
- Are you sure this is how they did it?

383
00:40:11,576 --> 00:40:14,090
Yes. It's all written down in the notes.

384
00:40:14,176 --> 00:40:17,168
Now tie offthe kites
and hurry down as fast as you can.

385
00:40:17,256 --> 00:40:18,689
What's the hurry?

386
00:40:18,776 --> 00:40:22,564
There's a possibility of electrocution.
Do you understand?

387
00:40:26,216 --> 00:40:29,970
I say: "There's a possibility of electrocution."

388
00:40:30,496 --> 00:40:32,851
Do you understand?

389
00:40:32,936 --> 00:40:35,848
I understand, I understand.
Why are you shouting?

390
00:40:36,976 --> 00:40:38,568
Did you...

391
00:40:39,496 --> 00:40:42,294
- Did you tie offthe kites?
- Of course.

392
00:40:43,576 --> 00:40:45,567
All right. Good.

393
00:40:47,736 --> 00:40:50,455
- Check the generator.
- Yes, master.

394
00:40:57,896 --> 00:40:59,124
I-gor,

395
00:40:59,216 --> 00:41:02,526
- release the safety valve on the main wheel.
- Yes, master.

396
00:41:08,336 --> 00:41:12,693
Can you imagine the brain
of Hans Delbruck in this body?

397
00:41:12,776 --> 00:41:14,687
Oh, Frederick.

398
00:41:15,176 --> 00:41:17,167
This is the moment.

399
00:41:18,096 --> 00:41:20,087
Well, dear...

400
00:41:20,176 --> 00:41:22,167
Are you ready?

401
00:41:22,256 --> 00:41:24,247
Yes, Doctor.

402
00:41:25,616 --> 00:41:27,607
Elevate me.

403
00:41:28,296 --> 00:41:30,287
Now? Right here?

404
00:41:32,016 --> 00:41:35,691
- Yes, yes. Raise the platform.
- Oh, the platform.

405
00:41:35,776 --> 00:41:37,971
Oh, that. Ja... yes.

406
00:41:56,336 --> 00:42:00,693
From that fateful day
when stinking bits of slime

407
00:42:00,776 --> 00:42:05,292
first crawled from the sea
and shouted to the cold stars:

408
00:42:05,896 --> 00:42:08,456
"I am man",

409
00:42:09,736 --> 00:42:14,287
our greatest dread has always been
the knowledge of our own mortality.

410
00:42:15,016 --> 00:42:17,007
But tonight

411
00:42:17,096 --> 00:42:19,769
we shall hurl the gauntlet of science

412
00:42:19,856 --> 00:42:23,326
into the frightful face of death itself.

413
00:42:25,576 --> 00:42:27,567
Tonight,

414
00:42:27,776 --> 00:42:31,564
we shall ascend into the heavens.

415
00:42:32,136 --> 00:42:34,969
We shall mock the earthquake.

416
00:42:35,616 --> 00:42:38,084
We shall command the thunders

417
00:42:38,856 --> 00:42:40,847
and penetrate

418
00:42:40,936 --> 00:42:47,330
into the very womb
of impervious nature herself.

419
00:42:55,256 --> 00:42:58,885
When I give the word,
throw the first switch.

420
00:42:59,376 --> 00:43:01,367
You've got it, master.

421
00:43:05,296 --> 00:43:07,287
Get ready.

422
00:43:10,056 --> 00:43:11,933
Get set.

423
00:43:12,016 --> 00:43:13,768
Go!

424
00:43:19,496 --> 00:43:21,691
Throw the second switch.

425
00:43:26,056 --> 00:43:28,570
Throw the third switch.

426
00:43:28,656 --> 00:43:31,011
Not the third switch?

427
00:43:31,096 --> 00:43:34,054
Throw it, I say. Throw it!

428
00:43:45,576 --> 00:43:47,567
Life.

429
00:43:47,656 --> 00:43:50,170
Life, do you hear me?

430
00:43:50,256 --> 00:43:52,247
Give my creation

431
00:43:52,936 --> 00:43:55,325
Iife!

432
00:44:16,536 --> 00:44:18,970
Turn everything off and bring me down.

433
00:45:26,136 --> 00:45:28,127
Nothing.

434
00:45:28,536 --> 00:45:30,970
- Oh, Doctor. I'm sorry...
- No, no.

435
00:45:31,736 --> 00:45:34,455
Be of good cheer.

436
00:45:34,536 --> 00:45:37,334
If science teaches us anything,

437
00:45:37,416 --> 00:45:40,852
it teaches us to accept our failures

438
00:45:40,936 --> 00:45:43,370
as well as our successes

439
00:45:44,016 --> 00:45:47,292
with quiet dignity

440
00:45:48,736 --> 00:45:50,966
and grace.

441
00:46:00,736 --> 00:46:03,204
Son of a bitch, bastard. I'll get you for this.

442
00:46:03,296 --> 00:46:05,287
What did you do to me?

443
00:46:05,376 --> 00:46:08,971
- What did you do to me?
- Doctor, stop it!

444
00:46:09,056 --> 00:46:10,887
You'll kill him!

445
00:46:12,216 --> 00:46:13,808
I don't wanna live.

446
00:46:13,896 --> 00:46:17,127
I do not want to live.

447
00:46:19,296 --> 00:46:21,890
Quiet dignity and grace.

448
00:46:22,816 --> 00:46:24,852
Mama!

449
00:46:26,216 --> 00:46:29,765
Oh, tosh! This man is different, I tell you.

450
00:46:29,856 --> 00:46:33,485
You can see that after you've
talked to him for five minutes.

451
00:46:35,416 --> 00:46:36,974
Yes?

452
00:46:38,456 --> 00:46:40,447
He's a Frankenstein!

453
00:46:40,536 --> 00:46:43,653
And they're all alike.

454
00:46:44,336 --> 00:46:46,770
It's in their blood. They can't 'elp it.

455
00:46:47,256 --> 00:46:49,850
All those scientists, they're all alike.

456
00:46:50,536 --> 00:46:52,527
They say they're working for us.

457
00:46:52,816 --> 00:46:56,695
What they really want is to rule the world.

458
00:47:02,976 --> 00:47:07,174
That's enough now. I will not have
this meeting become a free-for-all.

459
00:47:07,256 --> 00:47:10,009
These are very serious charges
you're making,

460
00:47:10,096 --> 00:47:14,965
and all the more painful to us, your elders,
because we still have nightmares

461
00:47:15,056 --> 00:47:17,650
from five times before.

462
00:47:18,376 --> 00:47:24,326
Now, we haven't heard from the one man
most qualified to judge the situation fairly.

463
00:47:25,856 --> 00:47:27,847
Inspector Kemp.

464
00:47:28,896 --> 00:47:31,205
Will you talk to us, please?

465
00:47:57,816 --> 00:48:01,286
A riot is an ugly thing

466
00:48:01,376 --> 00:48:05,608
undonce you get one started

467
00:48:05,696 --> 00:48:08,654
there is little chance of stopping it

468
00:48:09,416 --> 00:48:11,805
short of bloodshed.

469
00:48:12,696 --> 00:48:17,724
I think before we go around killing people,

470
00:48:17,856 --> 00:48:23,249
we had better make damn sure
of our evidence.

471
00:48:24,656 --> 00:48:26,647
Und...

472
00:48:30,776 --> 00:48:34,086
..we had better confirm the fact

473
00:48:34,176 --> 00:48:38,055
that young Frankenstein is indeed

474
00:48:38,136 --> 00:48:41,208
vollowing in his grandfather's vootstaps.

475
00:48:41,296 --> 00:48:42,411
What?

476
00:48:42,496 --> 00:48:45,374
Vollowing in his grandfather's vootstaps.
Vootstaps.

477
00:48:45,456 --> 00:48:46,889
Oh, footsteps.

478
00:48:46,976 --> 00:48:48,967
I think

479
00:48:49,056 --> 00:48:51,286
what is in order

480
00:48:53,096 --> 00:48:57,886
is for me to pay a little visit
on the good doctor

481
00:48:58,456 --> 00:49:03,974
undto have a nice, quiet chat.

482
00:49:08,776 --> 00:49:10,573
Reputation.

483
00:49:10,856 --> 00:49:12,847
Reputation.

484
00:49:13,776 --> 00:49:16,973
Oh, Doctor. You mustn't do this to yourself.

485
00:49:18,056 --> 00:49:20,365
You've got to stop thinking about it.

486
00:49:20,976 --> 00:49:23,888
Why, look.
You haven't even touched your food.

487
00:49:25,856 --> 00:49:27,209
There.

488
00:49:28,456 --> 00:49:30,811
Now I've touched it. Happy?

489
00:49:32,456 --> 00:49:35,448
You know... I'll never forget my old dad.

490
00:49:36,376 --> 00:49:41,052
When these things would happen to him...
the things he'd say to me.

491
00:49:42,536 --> 00:49:44,492
What did he say?

492
00:49:44,576 --> 00:49:47,534
What the hell are you doin'
in the bathroom day and night?

493
00:49:47,616 --> 00:49:51,086
Why don't you get outta there
and give someone else a chance?

494
00:49:57,176 --> 00:50:00,168
Oh, maybe it's better this way.

495
00:50:00,256 --> 00:50:02,690
The poor lifeless hulk.

496
00:50:02,776 --> 00:50:05,688
Maybe it is better off dead.

497
00:50:23,936 --> 00:50:25,654
What is this?

498
00:50:25,736 --> 00:50:27,727
SchwarzwalderKirschtorte.

499
00:50:30,096 --> 00:50:34,726
Do you like it? I'm not partial to
desserts myself, but this is excellent.

500
00:50:34,816 --> 00:50:37,205
Who are you talking to?

501
00:50:37,576 --> 00:50:41,808
To you. You just made a yummy sound,
so I thought you liked the dessert.

502
00:50:41,896 --> 00:50:44,933
I didn't make a yummy sound.
I just asked you what it is.

503
00:50:45,016 --> 00:50:48,133
- But you did. I just heard it.
- It wasn't me.

504
00:50:48,216 --> 00:50:50,207
It wasn't me.

505
00:50:50,296 --> 00:50:53,891
Well, now, look here.
If it wasn't you and it wasn't you...

506
00:51:15,456 --> 00:51:18,687
Alive. It's alive.

507
00:51:19,416 --> 00:51:22,010
It's alive!

508
00:51:24,496 --> 00:51:26,726
Stand back.

509
00:51:33,816 --> 00:51:36,376
Hello, there.

510
00:51:36,456 --> 00:51:39,414
I'm going to set you free.

511
00:51:41,616 --> 00:51:44,176
- Is the sedative ready?
- Yes, Doctor.

512
00:51:58,016 --> 00:52:00,007
I want you

513
00:52:00,736 --> 00:52:03,534
to sit up.

514
00:52:17,256 --> 00:52:21,044
Stand on your feet.

515
00:52:25,216 --> 00:52:27,446
You can do it.

516
00:52:36,576 --> 00:52:39,488
Now walk.

517
00:52:46,296 --> 00:52:48,571
